</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F0AFFE70BFCFEA9FB3EFD85" blockId="116.[189,1399,360,633]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE70BFCFEA9FEAFFE7F" allCaps="true" box="[189,287,361,387]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">THORAX.</emphasis>
Scutum inconspicuously microtrichose, setulae inconspicuous, except for a densely setulose patch on each side of anterior margin. Cervical sclerite oblong, with a small, depressed anterior portion; posterior portion elevated, with a large, whitish oval patch(probably a dense field of sensillae).Prosternum microtrichose and conspicuously setulose. Postpronotal lobe almost bare, very sparsely microtrichose and very sparsely setulose, anterior surface vertical and shiny along dorsal margin, posterior surface almost vertical and microtrichose, except for ventral carina. Dorsocentral and scutellar bristles absent. Vertical row of katepisternal bristles black. Katatergite weakly swollen, without median process, evenly convex and microtrichose. All coxae with an anteroventral tuft of long black setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F0AFFE70BFCFD59FA92FC9F" blockId="116.[189,1399,664,867]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE70BFCFD59FE82FD4F" allCaps="true" box="[189,306,665,691]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">ABDOMEN.</emphasis>
Abdominal segment 1 petiolate on basal half only, T2 short and expanded posteriorly. T3–5 narrow and depressed relative to T2 and T6. Pleuron greatly expanded on segments 3–5, micosetulose on dorsal third. Bursa with a small subquadrate body with a small and distal ventral receptacle, both spermathecal ducts arising separately from apex of bursa. Both ducts lead to paired spermathecae, with one duct and one pair of spermathecae slightly larger than the other. The smaller spermathecae are narrow and long, on short stems; the larger spermathecae are short, on longer convoluted stems.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368C7A86F0AFFE70BFCFC4AFD2CFAAA" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F0AFFE70BFCFC4AFE9FFC58" blockId="116.[189,303,906,932]" box="[189,303,906,932]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
<heading id="D085234F6F0AFFE70BFCFC4AFE9FFC58" bold="true" box="[189,303,906,932]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE70BFCFC4AFE9FFC58" bold="true" box="[189,303,906,932]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F0AFFE70BFCFC79FD2CFAAA" blockId="116.[189,1399,953,1366]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
The equal length spermathecal ducts, four spermathecae, reduced head bristles, and relatively nonpetiolate abdominal base (only the basal part of segment one is narrowed) of this species are atypical for 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F0AFFE70BFCFBC0FEF9FBE5" box="[189,329,1024,1049]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE70BFCFBC0FEF9FBE5" box="[189,329,1024,1049]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Mesoconius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as is the extended lower frons that covers part of the antennal socket. The general habitus, combined with a short oviscape, heavily pigmented wings and large size, are typical of the genus, but male specimens are needed to confirm this placement. Sequence data suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F0AFFE70F26FB86FAA9FBA3" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[1127,1305,1093,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadritheca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE70F26FB86FAA9FBA3" box="[1127,1305,1093,1119]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">M. quadritheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F0AFFE70E5FFB86FAC7FB9C" box="[1310,1399,1094,1120]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs firmly in the genus, close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F0AFFE709D3FBAAFD4FFB7F" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[658,767,1130,1155]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE709D3FBAAFD4FFB7F" box="[658,767,1130,1155]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">M. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F0AFFE7084AFBA9FCDBFB7F" box="[779,875,1129,1155]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F0AFFE708C1FBA9FC6AFB78" box="[896,986,1129,1156]" name="Bolivia" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F0AFFE70F64FBAAFB1DFB7F" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[1061,1197,1129,1155]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficrus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE70F64FBAAFB1DFB7F" box="[1061,1197,1129,1155]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">M. ruficrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F0AFFE70FFBFBA9FAAAFB7F" box="[1210,1306,1129,1155]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F0AFFE70E6FFBA9FADAFB7F" box="[1326,1386,1129,1155]" name="Peru" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Peru</collectingCountry>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F0AFFE70BFCFB4DFE6FFB5A" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,479,1164,1190]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadritheca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE70BFCFB4DFE6FFB5A" box="[189,479,1164,1190]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Mesoconius quadritheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F0AFFE70AA6FB4CFDF2FB5A" box="[487,578,1164,1190]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to, and obviously closely related to, 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F0AFFE70F2AFB4DFB63FB5A" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[1131,1235,1165,1190]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE70F2AFB4DFB63FB5A" box="[1131,1235,1165,1190]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">M. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F0AFFE70F9AFB4CFA86FB5A" box="[1243,1334,1164,1190]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F0AFFE70BFCFB6FFEA3FB35" box="[189,275,1199,1225]" name="Bolivia" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. These species share the very unusual possession of four spermathecae, limited constriction at the abdominal base, narrowed T3–5, setose prosternum, and similar colour and general habitus, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F0AFFE70BFCFB36FE93FAF3" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,291,1270,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE70BFCFB36FE93FAF3" box="[189,291,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">M. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F0AFFE70A6BFB36FE33FAEC" box="[298,387,1270,1296]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F0AFFE7095DFB36FD60FAF3" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[540,720,1269,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadritheca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE7095DFB36FD60FAF3" box="[540,720,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">M. quadritheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F0AFFE70996FB36FC81FAEC" box="[727,817,1270,1296]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having well-developed vertical and postocellar bristles (present but minute in 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F0AFFE7095DFADAFD60FACF" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[540,720,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadritheca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE7095DFADAFD60FACF" box="[540,720,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">M. quadritheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F0AFFE70994FAD9FC83FACF" box="[725,819,1305,1331]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F0AFFE70804FADAFB82FACF" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[837,1074,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficrus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F0AFFE70804FADAFB82FACF" box="[837,1074,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Mesoconius ruficrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F0AFFE70F79FAD9FB22FACF" box="[1080,1170,1305,1331]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
seems to be closely related, but has only three spermathecae.
</paragraph>
